textBeforeTable: On the Field Off the Field: Born September 7, 1987...Daughter of Edward and Katherine Brewster...Has a sister, Jocelyn (28), and a brother, BJ (26)...Favorite movies are "Troy" and "Pretty Woman"...Favorite book is "Angels and Demons" by Dan Brown...Favorite sports personality is Jerry Rice...Has set a goal in life to play soccer professionally...Majoring in Civil Engineering. Career: 2008: Third Team All-Mid-Atlantic Region...Second Team All-CAA defender...Matched career-high in points with 11 on four goals and three assists...Notched game-winning overtime goal as time expired against George Washington University, leading to a National Team of the Week honor...Anchored one of the leagues best defenses, assisting in 11 team shutouts and a CAA-best 0.82 goals against average. 2007: Started all 17 games for the Monarchs...Scored a career-high five goals and tallied a career-high 11 points on the season...Scored the game-winner against Drexel...Helped anchor the Lady Monarch defense before being asked to move upfield as a scoring presence...Had goals in five straight games to help ODU open the season with a 5-2-1 record. 2006: Started all 23 games for the Monarchs...Scored two goals and tallied one assist for five points...Scored the game-winner against Hofstra...Had a .500 on-goal shot percentage. 2005: Played in all 19 games with nine starts...scored a goal vs. UNCG...
